<TITLE> Manzur's mother dies </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, May 24 (bdnews24.com)  The mother of M Manzur Alam, the BNP-backed mayoral candidate for Chittagong City Corporation polls, died early on Monday. Mostafa Khatun died at her Uttar Kattali residence in the port city at around 2:30am. She was 82. Manzur's personal assistant Abdur Rahim said that Mostafa Khatun had been suffering from cancer for a long time. She leaves behind four sons and two daughters. On hearing the news, leaders and activists of Chittagong Metropolitan BNP thronged to the house to sympathise with the bereaved family. The namaj-e-janaza of Mostafa Khatun will be held at Mostafa Hakim Degree College in Uttar Kattali at 2pm today. Chittagong BNP leaders and activists and Awami League CCC mayoral candidate, ABM Mohiuddin Chowdhury, are expected to attend the janaza. bdn
